# Payload CMS Conventions

## Collections & Globals

- Collections in `src/payload/collections/`
- Globals in `src/payload/globals/`
- One file per collection/global
- Use TypeScript types generated by Payload (`payload-types.ts`)

## Fields

- Use `name` in camelCase
- Add `label` in English (Payload admin is English-only)
- Always set `required: true` when the field is mandatory
- Group related fields with `tabs` or `group` field types

## Media

- All uploads go through the `Media` collection
- Use `sharp` for image optimization (already configured)
- Provide `alt` text field on every image

## Access Control

- Admin-only by default
- Public read access where needed via `access.read: () => true`

## Hooks

- `afterChange` hooks for revalidation (when implemented)
- Keep hooks in separate files if complex
